            "story": "Sean Thackrey \"Orion\" St. Helena Proprietary Red 2008\n\nSean’s greatest wine is of course Orion, from St. Helena’s 102-yearold Rossi vineyard. Though the ancient vines are shrouded in mystery, Sean believes that most of Rossi is planted to an old Syrah clone imported from the northern Rhône in the 1870s. Orion’s grandeur has drawn comparison to such greats as Guigal La Mouline and Chave Hermitage. Steve Tanzer calls it “one of the world’s easiest wines to pick out in a blind tasting”.\n\nMarching to the beat of a drummer largely unknown to any other winemaker in California, Sean Thackerey continues to produce some extraordinary wines, in this case from a field blend planted in 1905. This is clearly a Rhone Ranger blend, with a dense ruby/purple color and loads of incense, camphor, blue and black fruits, earth, and spice. Full-bodied, rich, and bursting with personality, the wine is unique/singular, with an intensity that has to be tasted to be believed. \n95 points Robert Parker's Wine Advocate \n",
