            "story": "Buoncristiani Sauvignon Blanc (Napa Valley, CA) 2012.  \n\nThe Buoncristiani brothers, (there are 4 of them), grew up helping their father, (a school administrator), make wine around the house.  Dad even won a gold medal for his 1974 Petite Sirah.  However, Dad did not wish his sons to grow up to be winemakers.  In 1995, after going to school for, and starting careers in medicine, the two oldest brothers began making wine together.  After winning some local, California prizes, the duo's younger brothers joined them to start California's smallest bonded winery.  Moving the cars out of the garage during harvest, in order to make wine, the brothers soon created quite a stir with world-class wines. With experience at Rudd, Hess, and working under uber-consultant Philippe Melka, the Buoncristiani Brothers are bringing a wealth of experience to bear.  Complex aromas of lemon zest, ripe ruby grapefruit, jalapeno jam, orange sherbert, floral muscat, vanilla, and lemon cream pie entice the senses.  On the palate, a creamy texture leads the way to layered flavors of mango, green melon, nectarine, key lime pie, honeysuckle and vanilla wafer.  Zesty citrus flavors, tropical fruit and ultra bright acidity linger in the crisp and clean finish.  Not yet rated.",
