            "story": "The Crane Assembly G.B. Crane Vineyard El Coco, \nSt Helena, Napa, CA\n\nBig and Bold! Dave Phinney's (The Prisoner) new project.\n\n47% Zinfandel, 42% Petite Sirah, 9% Merlot, 2% Cabernet Sauvignon\n\nThe Crane Assembly is centered around a unique eight-acre vineyard located in the gravel rich soils of southern St. Helena. It is believed that George Beldon Crane, or simply G.B. Crane, first established grapes on this site in the year 1885, making it one of the oldest vineyards in the Napa Valley.\n\nOf the eight acres in production, approximately four acres are Crane’s original plantings. This four-acre block has been continuously farmed for nearly one hundred and thirty years.\n\nBold and concentrated. Rich aromatics of dark stone fruits and soft French oak mingle together to frame a very sophisticated entry with more than ample weight. The bright mid-pallet is replete with waves of concentration. High tones of ripe cherries and cassis come together and coat the mouth in richness.\n\n92 Points from Bones Staff",
