            "story": "Montevetrano (Campania, IT) 2007.  \n\n60% Cabernet Sauvignon / 30% Merlot / 10% Aglianico.  Owner Silvia Imparato started to make wine as a hobby.  She grafted Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, & Aglianico onto old, existing rootstock on the family property.  With the help of Riccardo Coterella she has fashioned a modern, oak-aged wine that helped to change the wine world by showing that quality wine could come from Southern Italy.  Though there are more wines from the region, now, hers is still the best.  The 2007 Montevetrano is the product of an unusual vintage characterized by hot temperatures that were virtually uninterrupted throughout the year. Bright red fruit, flowers and spices are some of the nuances that emerge from this silky, beautifully balanced Montevetrano. The combination of explosive ripe fruit, richness and finesse is utterly breathtaking. The warmth of the vintage comes through in the wine’s generosity, yet there are no suggestions whatsoever of over- ripeness. This is a magnificent Montevetrano. Robert Parker 95 points.",
