            "story": "Dolcetto D'Alba - Dolcetto (Piedmont, Italy) 2012.  \n\nPrunotto (the winery behind this Prunotto Dolcetto d’Alba) has seen a dramatic expansion in the last 20 years. Originally run by Alfredo Prunotto, who setup Prunotto from the ruins of the “Ai Vini delle Langhe\" co-operative in 1923 and later run by the well known winemaker Beppe Colla. In 1989 Prunotto began to co-operate with the Tuscany-based Marchesi Antonori family – a co-operation that led to the purchase of Prunotto by the Marchesi Antinori family in 1994.\n\nThis wine is from Italy, Piedmont region, Dolcetto D'alba sub-region. Ruby red in colour. On the nose, fragrant, fruity bouquet with hints of flowers. This is a very versatile piedmontese wine and a perfect match for a variety of dishes.",
