            "story": "Twomey Merlot (Napa, CA) 2009. 94% Merlot, 5.6% Cabernet Franc, 0.4% Cabernet Sauvignon. \n\nTwomey Cellars is a project owned by Silver Oak and started by Daniel Baron, who took over for founding winemaker, Justin Meyer. Baron has been at Silver Oak since 1994 and previously worked in Bordeaux—most notably at Chateau Petrus (including the superb 1982 vintage). This is single vineyard Merlot from the Soda Canyon Ranch in Napa (originally purchased for Cabernet to blend into the Silver Oak Napa). Twomey now has a winery in Calistoga. Day to day winemaking is overseen by Christina Pällman, who worked with Michel Rolland at Le Bon Pasteur in Bordeaux, at Domaine Dujac in Burgundy, at Felton road in New Zealand, at Luna with John Kongsgaard, & is the wine maker at Fritz Winery. This Merlot has a dark garnet color and heady aromas of black cherry compote, nutmeg, roasting coffee and violets that seem to burst from the glass. It has a bright entry and a soft, velvety, mouth-coating, mid-palate replete with flavors of juicy berries, roasting coffee and a hint of dark chocolate. This full-bodied, complex wine lingers on the palate with a long, harmonious finish.  Not yet rated.",
