            "story": "Williams Selyem \"Unoaked\" Chardonnay (Russian River, CA) 2010.  \n\nJohn & Kathe Dyson bought Williams Selyem from its original owners in 1998.  As well as owning wineries in New York, California, & Tuscany, the Dysons were customer #2080 on the Williams Selyem mailing list.  Winemaker Bob Cabral, (De Loach, Kunde, Alderbrook, Hartford Court), was customer #576, on the Williams Selyem mailing list, before becoming wine maker in 1998.  The Vineyard: The chardonnay for this blend was sourced from the Allen Vineyard, the Drake Estate Vineyard, the Hawk Hill Vineyard, the Heintz Vineyard, the Olivet Lane Vineyard, and the Lazy W Ranch on Westside Road.  This 100% stainless steel fermented, no malo-lactic wine exhibits what chardonnay REALLY tastes like from the Russian River Valley. It has sweet aromas of tree-ripened white nectarines, Red Haven peaches, Gravenstein apples and citrus blossoms. Similar flavors of ripe stone fruits, guava, passion fruit and wet stone coat your palate.  ",
