            "story": "Savigny Lès Beaune - Domaine Pavelot \"Dominode\" (Premier Cru)  2013\nBurgundy, FR\n\nThe Pavelots have been cultivating vines in Savigny-lès-Beaune just before the French revolution and have made some of the best wines in the village since. The domaine’s flagship, La Dominode, is powerfully structured wine from the south hill of Savigny. \n\nSavigny-lès-Beaune is a northern commune in Burgundy’s Côte de Beaune. Red wine from Pinot Noir makes up 85% of the production. The village doesn’t have Grand Crus, though there are 22 classified Premier Crus. The commune is enclosed by the hills of Corton and Côte de Beaune on either side creating sites with many different exposures. \n\n\"This is aromatically reserved but through aggressive swirling eventually coaxes notes of spiced plum, earth and an array of various dark berries from the glass. There is a velvety and caressing mouth feel to the vibrant mineral-driven medium weight flavors that possess good energy.\" \n\n90 Points from Vinous",
