            "story": "Faust \"The Pact\"  Cabernet Sauvignon 2013\nNapa Valley\n\nFaust is one of projects under the Quintessa umbrella and the Agustin Huneeus family.\n\nThe Pact is Cabernet Sauvignon from primarily Coombsville and Rutherford, but some other small lots are in the blend, according to winemaker Charles Thomas, who has an impressive resumé, having worked at Rudd Estate as well as Robert Mondavi. The wine ratchets up the levels of richness, displaying a deep purple color and notes of pen ink, crème de cassis and vanilla in a medium to full-bodied, impressive style.\n\nIntrigued by the structure and depth provided by these vines, we began to explore ways to elevate their beauty and richness by complementing them with handpicked selections from high quality vineyards in Rutherford, Mt. Veeder, Atlas Peak and other parts of Napa Valley. \n\nA dense and chewy wine with lots of blueberry and blackberry character. Full body, lots of fruit and concentration.",
