            "story": "Cliff Lede “Poetry” Cabernet Sauvignon 2007 \nStags Leap District, Napa, California\n\nCanadian businessman, (construction development), Cliff Lede, (pronounced lay-dee), started the winery in 2002.  There is an art gallery on the property, & the luxury inn has the same name as this luxury cuvee—Poetry.  Vineyard blocks are named after “classic” rock songs.  Superstar vineyard manager David Abreu and consultant Michel Rolland oversee the 60 acres of vines as well as the gravity-fed wine and sorting system developed at Chateau LaTour.  Winemaker Michelle Edwards spent 3 years at Colgin. One of the best Napa Cabernets at the price.  \n\nThe quintessential expression of an elegant Stags Leap Cabernet Sauvignon, the 2007 Cabernet Sauvignon Poetry combines elegance with power. Layered and full-bodied with an ethereal lightness as well as touches of oak and tannin, it is gorgeously pure and textured yet strikingly long and intense. Bursting with flavor, but neither heavy nor cloying.  \n\nRobert Parker 96 points.  \nWine Spectator 91 points. ",
