            "year": "2011",
            "bin_number": "281",
            "story": "Hourglass Cabernet Sauvignon 2011\n\nOwned by Jeff and Carolyn Smith, they have Bob Foley as their winemaker.(Robert Foley, Pride, Switchback Ridge, and School House) Hourglass takes its name from the fact that the vineyard defines the \"pinch,\" or narrowest part of the hourglass shaped Napa Valley. In the summer of 2001 with the first case ever sold, David Stevens and Karen Williams, then the wine directors at Tra Vigne restaurant in St. Helena, included Hourglass in a 1997 flight tasting during the week of the Napa Valley Wine Auction. The flight included Screaming Eagle, Bryant Family and Harlan Estate. Tasted by 25 collectors and wine trade professionals, Hourglass never ranked lower than third in the flight! This tasting set in motion an avalanche of interest in Hourglass, which has been growing steadily ever since.\n\nDespite the cooler vintage, Cabernet Sauvignon in the Hourglass Estate Vineyard achieved optimal levels of phenolic and tannin ripeness, resulting in pure fruit extraction, supple textures, and exotic aromas. The hallmark aromatics of mint, camphor and black licorice are all present, as well as those of woody elements including cedar and sandalwood.  Exhibiting the classically delineated structure of a cooler season, the wine features a tight-knit core of dark red and black fruit flavors evoking pomegranate, cassis, and a tangy acidity. The wine showcases grace and finesse, with ample richness, a compelling mouth feel and lingering finish.  \n\n",
